SAMPLE CHEAT SHEET ONE PAGE

### üîπ Navigation
| Command | Purpose | Example |
|--------|--------|--------|
| `ls` | List files | `ls` |
| `ls -l` | List with details | `ls -l` |
| `ls -a` | Show hidden files | `ls -a` |
| `cd dir` | Change directory | `cd Documents` |
| `cd ..` | Go up | `cd ..` |
| `cd ~` | Home dir | `cd ~` |
| `pwd` | Show path | `pwd` |

---

### üîπ File & Dir Management
| Command | Purpose | Example |
|--------|--------|--------|
| `mkdir dir` | Create dir | `mkdir projects` |
| `mkdir -p path` | Nested dirs | `mkdir -p work/reports` |
| `touch file.txt` | Create file | `touch notes.txt` |
| `cp src dst` | Copy | `cp file.txt backup/` |
| `mv old new` | Move/rename | `mv old.txt new.txt` |
| `rm file.txt` | Delete | `rm old.txt` |
| `rm -r dir/` | Delete dir | `rm -r backup/` |
| `rm -f file.txt` | Force delete | `rm -f temp.txt` |

---

### üîπ View & Search
| Command | Purpose | Example |
|--------|--------|--------|
| `cat file.txt` | Show content | `cat README.md` |
| `head file.txt` | First 10 lines | `head log.txt` |
| `tail file.txt` | Last 10 lines | `tail app.log` |
| `grep "text" file.txt` | Search text | `grep "error" app.log` |
| `echo "Hello"` | Print text | `echo "Hi!"` |

---

### üîπ Tools & Shortcuts
| Command | Purpose |
|--------|--------|
| `clear` | Clear screen |
| `history` | Show commands |
| `!!` | Re-run last |
| `man cmd` | Manual | `man grep` |
| `Ctrl + C` | Cancel |
| `Ctrl + D` | Exit |

---

### üí° Pro Tips:
- **Tab** ‚Üí auto-complete filenames  
- `--help` ‚Üí quick help: `ls --help`  
- `Ctrl + R` ‚Üí search command history  

du -sh --shows disk usage of the current directory in a human-readable format.

PS1 defines the command prompt ‚Äî what appears before you type a command.

It controls the text and formatting of the prompt, including:

Username
Hostname
Current directory
Color
The % or # symbol

